# S-FET: Spin FET Based on Graphene Nanoribbon

A MATLAB simulation of a **Spin Field-Effect Transistor (Spin-FET)** built on 
Graphene Nanoribbon (GNR) in the presence of **surface roughness**.

## Overview

This project investigates quantum transport in GNR-based Spin-FETs using:
- **Tight-Binding (TB)** models for electronic structure
- **Non-Equilibrium Green's Function (NEGF)** formalism for transport
- **Rashba spin-orbit coupling** analysis
- Surface roughness modeling and its effect on spin polarization and conductance

## Methods

| Tool | Purpose |
|---|---|
| MATLAB | Core simulation environment |
| Tight-Binding model | Electronic band structure of GNR |
| Green's functions | Quantum transport calculations |
| Rashba effect | Spin-orbit interaction modeling |

## Context

Developed as part of the MSc thesis work at the University of Mohaghegh Ardabili, 
